<SECOND>PM-Starless Walk,0210</SECOND>
<HEAD>Commission Says No To Hard Rock Cafe Star Walk</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Hard Rock Cafe is going to try again to
persuade a city commission to allow a ``walk of fame'' on the
sidewalks surrounding the French Quarter rock 'n' roll eatery, a
spokeswoman said.
   ``They plan to resubmit their proposal, and for the moment have
pledged that the St. Louis Street side be dedicated to native New
Orleans musicians such as Fats Domino,'' said spokeswoman Barbara
Hutson in a news release Friday.
   The restaurant sought permission from a committee of the Vieux
Carre Commission on Thursday to install 10 to 12 brass plaques,
emblazoned with stars, as tributes to musicians who have visited the
Hard Rock.
   Similar sidewalk plaques have been installed at Hard Rock Cafes
in New York, Chicago and other cities.
   All five members of the Vieux Carre Commission's architecture
committee, expressed displeasure with the idea. The commission is
charged by the city with guarding the historic beauty and
architectural integrity of the French Quarter _ the oldest section
of the Mississippi River port city.
   Among the complaints: the quarter should not be home to memorials
for the living and sidewalks should not be used for advertising.
