<HEAD>Widow Of Late President Removed From Post</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAPUTO, Mozambique (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The widow of the late President Samora
Machel has been replaced as education minister, a Cabinet post she
held since Mozambique gained independent from Portugal in 1975, the
national news agency reported.
   Graca Machel's husband was president from 1975 until he died in
an airplane crash in South Africa in October 1986. He was replaced
by Joaquim Chissano.
   Chissano replaced Mrs. Machel on Friday with Aniceto dos
Muchangos, former director of the country's most important teacher
training body, the Higher Pedagogical Institute, the news agency AIM
said.
   No reason was given for the change.
   Mrs. Machel remains a member of the Central Committee of the
governing Frelimo Party, AIM said.
