<FIRST>r i AM-France-Quake     01-07 0113</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-France-Quake,0116</SECOND>
<HEAD>Tremor Reported In Southwestern Franc</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TARBES, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 15-second tremor shook the mountainous
southwestern region of France, but no injuries were reported,
officials said Saturday.
   The quake, measuring 4.2 on the Richter scale, hit at 8:33 p.m.
on Friday, said the officials.
   Its epicenter was at the ski station in La Mongie, in the
Pyrenees mountains that form the border between France and Spain.
   The tremor reportedly caused some cracks in buildings and rattled
furniture and other objects.
   The Richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on a
seismograph. An earthquake of 3.5 can cause slight damage and one
measuring 4 can cause moderate damage.
</TEXT>
