<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bjorn Borg, known for the silent,
determined style he displayed in winning five Wimbledon titles from
1976-80, plans to marry a colorful, Italian rock star, according to
published reports.
   Swedish newspapers reported Saturday that the 32-year-old Swede
will marry Italian singer Loredana Berte on Feb. 26 in Milan.
   The Aftonbladet daily said Borg had asked Loredana, a 38-year-old
rock star known for her wild and explicit stage appearances, several
times to become his wife before she agreed last December.
   ``Now Bjorn comes first and my career second,'' Loredana told the
newspaper Expressen. ``I am here in Sweden because I am in love, for
the rest of my life.''
   Borg, who has retired from active competition, earlier was
married to Romanian-born tennis player Mariana Simionescu. In 1984,
he met Jannike Bjorling, then 17 years old. She gave birth to their
son, Robin, a year later. They lived together until 1987.
