<HEAD>Girl Robs Elderly Man, Throw His Artificial Legs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A teen-age girl robbed a disabled
86-year-old man of his Social Security benefits, then threw his
artificial legs out of his reach so he could not pursue her, police
said.
   Alex Williams of Youngstown was sleeping at 2 a.m. Friday when
awakened by a girl he recognized as having robbed him two years
earlier, said Youngstown police Lt. Edward Zaccone.
   ``The girl removed his pants from him, (and) threw his two
artificial legs across the room,'' Zaccone said. The robber then
took $800 from Williams' wallet, he said. Williams was not injured.
   The suspect, a 15-year-old girl whom police did not identify, was
at large Saturday, Zaccone said.
   ``This is terrible,'' said Williams, a retired produce worker.
``Now I'm broke and can't pay my bills.''
