<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three Israelis beat and kidnapped a Palestinian
man on Saturday because they were upset about his romance with a
Jewish woman, a news report said.
   The assailants, relatives of the woman, broke into an apartment
in suburban Tel Aviv where the couple was staying, beat the
Palestinian man and hauled him away in the trunk of their car, the
Itim news agency said.
   The young woman fled and alerted a policeman, who pursued the
assailants' car and freed the 29-year-old Palestinian from the
trunk, Itim reported.
   Police took the beating victim to Tel Hashomer Hospital in Tel
Aviv, where he was treated for minor injuries and then released,
Itim said.
   The attackers, two men aged 44 and 22 and a 35-year-old woman,
were arrested and charged with kidnapping. All were residents of the
Tel Aviv suburb of Rosh Ha'ayin, Itim said.
   The assailants had apparently implored their relative, a divorced
woman in her late 20s, to leave her Arab boyfriend, a native of
Hebron in the Israeli-occupied West Bank, Itim said. The couple have
been romantically involved for two years, Itim said.
   Itim quoted the Palestinian boyfriend as saying, ``I don't see
what the fuss is all about. There is no difference between me and a
Jew.''
   A Tel Aviv police spokesman refused to confirm details of the
story.
