<HEAD>Security Stepped Up Around U.S. Bases On Crete</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HERAKLION, Crete (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Security has been stepped up near the two
U.S. military bases on this Greek island after they were threatened
in a note attached to an airport bomb, police said Saturday.
   The bomb was found Thursday at Heraklion International Airport
and dismantled by police, a police spokesman said.
   It carried a handwritten note signed by the ``Unknown
Organization.'' The group said it would attack the U.S. Air Force
