condition of anonymity in keeping with Greek practice.
   Relations between the United States and Libya have hit a new low
since U.S. jets downed two Libyan military planes and U.S. officials
began complaining about a factory in Libya they believe is designed
to make chemical weapons. President Reagan has said military action
against the plant is an option.
   More than 1,200 U.S. servicemen and 400 local employees work at
the military installation at Gournes, which monitors radio
communications and Soviet activity in the Mediterranean.
   The Gournes base and a U.S. Sixth Fleet supply installation at
Suda Bay are located about 150 miles from Libya.
   
  
